    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-08-23T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-08-23T13:00:00-05:00" n="362"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d362">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">835.796/164: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Armour</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-08-23T14:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 23, 1941—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>566. Your 829, August 12, 9 p.m.<note n="39" xml:id="d362fn1">Not printed.</note>
                        Harding<note n="40" xml:id="d362fn2">William Barclay Harding, vice president
                        of the Defense Supplies Corporatión, a buying agency of the Federal Loan
                        Agency.</note> has discussed Argentina’s commercial aviation problems with
                        Piñedo<note n="41" xml:id="d362fn3">Federico Piñedo, formerly Argentine
                        Minister of Finance.</note> and a memorandum of conversation<note n="39"
                        xml:id="d362fn4">Not printed.</note> is being forwarded to you by
                    airmail.</p>
                <p>It appears that Sana<note n="42" xml:id="d362fn5">Sociedad Argentina de
                        Navegación Aérea.</note> and Corporatión<note n="43" xml:id="d362fn6"
                        >Corporación Sudamericana de Servicios Aéreos.</note> will merge and that
                        Aeroposta<note n="44" xml:id="d362fn7">Aeroposta Argentina.</note> will be
                    forced to join by reason of availability to the merged organizations of
                    up-to-date American equipment.</p>
                <p>It is understood that either Wilcox or Oscar Muller will be authorized to handle
                    the financial arrangements on behalf of the Federal Loan Agency and that Piñedo
                    will assist in effecting the merger.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
